<p>"I shouldn't care so much." She made a fist and slammed it against the railing. "I don't <em>want to</em> care."</p>

<p>He stroked a damp curl from her cheek. "It's not a crime, Carly. Caring is who you are."</p>

<p>She gave a half-laugh, her eyes huge in the moonlit pallor of her face. "Thanks, I needed that."</p>

<p>"No," he said hoarsely. "What you need is this."</p>

