<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5>About the Author</h5>

<p>Christina Skye lives on the western slopes of the McDowell Mountains in Arizona. <em>Going Overboard</em> is her fifteenth novel, and her first set aboard a cruise ship. She enjoys the balmy Caribbean and the luminous Florida Keys, but her sharpest maritime memory dates to 1982, when a Chinese junk nearly tossed her headfirst into the gray spume of Kowloon Harbor. She still remembers how to scream "Watch out for the red sampan!" in Chinese.</p>

<p>Be sure to visit her online at: <a href="http://www.christinaskye.com"><em>www.christinaskye.com</em></a></p>
